\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 \ul \ulc0 README for KA Lite Mac OS X Application
\b0 \ulnone \
\
This is the KA Lite application that sits on the menu bar of Mac OS X.\
\
It is used to control and monitor the KA Lite server by Foundation for Learning Equality.\
\
It uses PyRun to isolate the KA Lite environment from your system's Python application.\
\
To install KA Lite\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Download the KA Lite Mac OS X Installer for 0.16 at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "0.16%5D(http://pantry.learningequality.org/downloads/ka-lite/0.16/installers/mac/)."}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 http://pantry.learningequality.org/downloads/ka-lite/0.16/installers/mac/.}}\
{\listtext	2.	}Double-click the downloaded `KA-Lite.pkg` package and follow the setup wizard.  The installation requires admin privileges.\
{\listtext	3.	}The installer will create the `/Applications/KA-Lite/` folder that contains the KA-Lite application, uninstaller tool, licence, readme, and release notes documents.\
{\listtext	4.	}The install process is quite lengthy because the installer had to copy assessment items and run some management commands including the setup process.  Please be patient.\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural
\cf0 \

\b Note:
\b0  A computer restart is needed to complete the installation.\
\
\

\b Using the KA Lite OS X Application
\b0 \
\
To start the KA Lite server:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Launch `KA-Lite` from the `/Applications/KA-Lite/` folder.\
{\listtext	2.	}Click the `KA-Lite` icon in the menu bar and select the `Start KA Lite` menu option.\
{\listtext	3.	}When prompted that KA Lite has been started, click on the icon again and select the `Open in Browser` menu option - this should launch KA Lite in your preferred web browser.\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural
\cf0 \
Menu Options:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}`Start KA Lite` - Starts the KA Lite web server.\
{\listtext	\'95	}`Stop KA Lite` - Stops the KA Lite web server.  This is available when the KA Lite server has started.\
{\listtext	\'95	}`Open in Browser` - Opens the installed KA Lite web app using your preferred web browser, usually at `http://127.0.0.1:8008`.  This is available when the KA Lite server has started.\
{\listtext	\'95	}`Preferences` - Opens the preferences window where you can customize the KA Lite data folder, view application logs in the `Logs` tab, or uninstall KA Lite.\
{\listtext	\'95	}`Quit` - Stops the KA Lite web server and closes the application.\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural
\cf0 \
How to set a custom KA Lite data folder:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls4\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Stop the KA Lite server from running.\
{\listtext	2.	}Set your custom KA Lite data folder in the `Preferences` dialog.\
{\listtext	3.	}Click `Apply`.  This will update the `KALITE_HOME` environment variable.\
{\listtext	4.	}Launch a new Terminal session to use the updated `KALITE_HOME` environment variable.\
{\listtext	5.	}Run `kalite manage syncdb --noinput`.\
{\listtext	6.	}Run `kalite manage init_content_items --overwrite`.\
{\listtext	7.	}Run `kalite manage unpack_assessment_zip /Users/Shared/ka-lite/assessment/assessment.zip`.\
{\listtext	8.	}Run `kalite manage setup --noinput`.\
{\listtext	9.	}Start the server again by clicking on `Start KA Lite` in the menu option.\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural
\cf0 \

\b Note:
\b0  You can specify another assessment items archive that you've downloaded at the `unpack_assessment_zip` step above, as long as it's compatible on this version of KA Lite.\
\
\
