\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}This will require admin privileges.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Double-click the `/Applications/KA-Lite/KA-Lite_Uninstall.tool`, this is a bash script that will do the following:\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural
\ls5\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}uninstall `KA-Lite.app` and remove its dependencies, then unset the environment variables.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}optionally remove the KA Lite data folder.\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural
